
'''MAPPS / M.A.P.P.S. -- Multi-laterally Assured Pervasive Permanent Sur-/Sous-veillance.''' 

Doctrine-concept coined and formulated by Philippe Van Nedervelde [http://www.foresight.org/about/VanNedervelde.html]. The acronym refers to and aims to supplant the Cold War era doctrine of M.A.D. (Mutually Assured Destruction) with a doctrine which aims to act as an effective deterrent of large-scale armed conflict. The MAPPS doctrine aims to do so not by virtue of a bi-lateral virtual parity of nuclear destructive capability as with M.A.D. in the Cold War era, but by a multi-lateral virtual parity of pervasive and permanent informational / intelligence capability realized by means of the anticipated development of extremely fine-grained intelligence gathering capability presumed to be in the form of nanotech-based so-called "Smart Dust" localizers. (See AetherWire, Inc. [http://www.aetherwire.com/], Dust Networks, Inc. [http://www.dustnetworks.com] and Panoptic Systems, Inc. [http://www.panopticsystems.com/])  The core concept / assumption is that if Everybody has Eyes & Ears Everywhere, then everyone is effectively stripped of the opportunity to plan and deploy any large-scale, organized armed aggressions against anyone else. The fulL MAPPS white-paper will be available here [placeholder to near-future link]. 

A.k.a. by the "Four E's": Everybody has Eyes & Ears Everywhere -- a sousveillance[http://www.p2pfoundation.net/index.php/Sousveillance]-favoring mnemonic coined by the same author.

